INSERT INTO `tests` VALUES (1,8,8,2,4,3,1075,'Primer Adherence Test',1,1,'QUAL','<p>The adherence of the <strong>primer</strong> to the steel surface shall be checked by a grid type scratch test, or pull type test, in accordance with ASTM standards or EN ISO equivalent.&nbsp;</p><p>The exact location, as well as the number of tests, shall be determined by the Administration.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-23 15:30:12','2023-12-23 15:56:20'),(2,8,8,2,4,3,1076,'Intermediate Coat Adhesion Test',1,1,'QUAL','<p>The adherence of the intermediate coat to the prime coat shall be checked by a grid type scratch test, or pull type test, in accordance with ASTM standards or EN ISO equivalent. The exact location, as well as the number of tests, shall be determined by the Administration.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-23 16:03:50','2023-12-23 16:03:50'),(3,8,8,2,4,3,1078,'Finish Coat Adhesion Test',1,1,'DEV','<p>The adherence of the finish coat to the prime coat shall be checked by a grid type scratch test or pull type test, in accordance with <a href=\"https://www.astm.org/\">ASTM Standards</a> or <a href=\"https://www.iso.org/home.html\">EN ISO</a> equivalent. The exact location, as well as the number of tests, shall be determined by the Administration.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-24 11:06:43','2023-12-24 11:08:26'),(4,8,8,2,4,3,1083,'Pressure Shell Welding Testing',1,1,'QUAL','<p>All complete joint penetration welds in the <strong>pressure shell components </strong>of the flexible nozzle assembly shall be 100% radiographically examined in accordance with ASME Boiler and Pressure Vessel Code, Section VIII, Division 1. Any applicable EN standards shall also be adhered to.</p><p>This test shall cover:</p><ul><li>All welds shall pass 100% \"<i>Dye Penetrant Test\"</i> (DPT) on final weldment prior to radiography, it is also recommended to apply DPT on the root pass of weld seams to prevent weld defects.</li><li>Weld acceptability, repairs and re-examination shall be as defined in ASME BPVC, Section VIII. Repairs to any welds rejected under examination shall be made, using qualified procedures and in a manner acceptable to the Engineer. Repaired welds shall be subjected to re-examination by spot radiography at a location designated by the Engineer</li><li>The Contractor shall submit a weld map indicating where 100% radiography will be conducted, for review by the Administration. Records of all such tests are to be submitted to the Administration for approval.</li></ul>','Verbatim','2023-12-25 17:47:12','2023-12-25 18:30:06'),(5,8,8,2,4,3,1084,'Shop Assembly Test for Jack Stations Sub-Assemblies',1,1,'QUAL','<p>The whole assembly shall be supported in an approximately horizontal plane on fixed<br>supports at the trunnion bearings and on roller supports at the inner cross beam. In this<br>position, the sub-assembly shall be extended and retracted by means of the hydraulic<br>cylinder with the screw stop nuts set at a minimum of three different positions spanning<br>the full range of their adjustments. flush hydraulic lines before the start of the test. A<br>temporary means for energizing and controlling the hydraulic system shall be provided.<br>The operation of the hydraulic system shall be tested at low pressure (17 barg). The jack<br>station sub-assemblies shall be secured on a bench fixture (Drawing 4281-245) and be<br>subjected to at least 20 complete cycles. 17 barg pressure shall be applied and be<br>measured over one cycle of maximum stroke during stopping and starting, every 50 mm<br>of stroke, see Drawing 4281-245. Also, for satisfactory operation, there shall be no<br>evidence of mechanical interferences, or any tendency for axes Y-Y and X-X, as defined<br>by Drawings 4281-245, not to remain parallel within the limits specified on the drawing.<br>The test shall be repeated with the assembly flipped over.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>With the assembly supported in the same position and extended to full length by the<br>hydraulic cylinder, the screw stop nuts shall be driven over their full range of adjustment,<br>by means of the input shaft on Drawings 4281-245, by hand with a means of measuring<br>the torque. The maximum torque shall not exceed 10 Nm. The test shall be repeated<br>with the assembly flipped over.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-26 18:33:17','2023-12-26 18:50:54'),(6,8,8,2,4,3,1085,'Shop Assembly Test for Screw Stop Drive Power Unit Sub-Assemblies ',1,1,'DEV','<p>The 38 screw stop drive power unit sub-assemblies shown on Drawing 4281-250 shall be<br>completely assembled on their base plates and tested as follows.<br>An operational test of both drive motors shall be conducted, using temporary electrical hookups,<br>to demonstrate the proper functioning of the equipment, including the gearboxes, the brake, the<br>clutch, the counter and the limit switches. Motor currents shall be logged for each drive.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-26 18:50:09','2023-12-26 18:58:23'),(7,8,8,2,4,3,1086,'Site Operating Tests for Jack Stations',1,1,'DEV','<p>After the structure has been erected and after the jack station sub-assemblies, the control<br>equipment and the complete hydraulic system have been installed but before the flexible plates<br>have been installed, the operation of each jack station sub-assembly shall be tested mechanically,<br>hydraulically, and electrically over its full range of operation, as follows:</p><ul><li>a) A temporary means for holding the jack station sub-assemblies in approximately correct<br>relative positions without the flexible plates installed shall be provided. In these positions,<br>each sub-assembly shall be extended and retracted by means of the hydraulic cylinder<br>with the screw stop nuts set at a minimum of three different positions spanning the full<br>range of their adjustments. The operation of the hydraulic system shall be tested at low<br>pressure (17 barg). The jack station sub-assemblies shall be secured on a bench fixture<br>(Drawing 4281-245) and be subjected to at least 20 complete cycles. 17 barg pressure<br>shall be applied and be measured over one cycle of maximum stroke during stopping and<br>starting, every 50 mm of stroke, see Drawing 4281-245. Also, for satisfactory operation,<br>there shall be no evidence of mechanical interferences, or any tendency for axes Y-Y and<br>X-X, as defined by Drawing 4281-245, not to remain parallel within the limits specified on<br>the drawing.</li><li>b) With the sub-assemblies still supported in the correct relative positions, the hydraulic<br>cylinders shall be fully extended, to the innermost contour position, and held there. The<br>Contractor shall then check for proper operation of the screw stops, at every jack station,<br>over the complete range of travel.</li></ul>','Verbatim','2023-12-26 19:01:39','2023-12-26 19:01:39'),(8,8,8,2,4,3,1087,'Site Operating Tests for Flexible Plates',1,1,'DEV','<p>The jack stations shall be cycled hydraulically at low pressure (under 17 barg) and at low speed,<br>to ascertain that the flexible plates are not subject to excessive curvature (i.e., overstressed) at<br>any time after the plates have been installed. For testing purposes, strain gauges or other<br>indicating devices may be used.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-26 19:06:13','2023-12-26 19:06:13'),(9,8,8,2,4,3,1088,'Site Operating Tests for Locking Pins',1,1,'DEV','<p>The locking pins (Drawing D4281-225), pipes, hoses, hydraulic cylinders (D4281-255/256) and<br>other hydraulic items shown on Drawing 4281-215 shall be cycled at least 20 times to ensure<br>ease of operation.</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-26 19:08:25','2023-12-26 19:08:25'),(10,8,8,2,4,3,1089,'Acceptance Tests for Tolerance Matching',1,1,'QUAL','<p>These acceptance tests should be performed to show compliance product\'s the matching to final tolerance (drawing 103) in the flex nozzle, relative moving parts working properly like jack station, flex plate, Hydraulic system, pneumatic seals.&nbsp;</p><p>The assembly should be able to interface with SC (fixed connection) on the upstream side within 103 drawing tolerance (in situ condition) and downstream TTS and Model cart arrangement (easy of assembly / disassembly and 103 drawing tolerances).&nbsp;</p><p>Additional tests may be proposed by client to the site contractor for final acceptance. The final acceptance tests shall be witnessed by the Owner and<br>the Engineer. Final acceptance by the Owner shall be contingent upon meeting all the equirements of this specification and drawings.<br>Detailed acceptance test procedures shall be provided at least one (1) month before the tests are scheduled and shall be subject to approval by the Owner.</p><p>Acceptance of the work will be upon satisfactory completion of all the work and supply as defined in this specification and drawings, including the completion of deficiencies and documentation. After the installation of the steel shell and components have been completed and the operating tests defined in this Specification have been performed, the Contractor shall, in conjunction with the Owner, conduct a set of acceptance tests under actual operating conditions, demonstrating that all components function and that the system operates as defined in this Specification. These acceptance tests shall be witnessed by the Owner.</p><p>If at any time during the tests or after satisfactory completion of the tests, any system indicates a malfunction, the Contractor shall make the necessary corrections and the tests repeated for that system.</p><p>The Owner or the Engineer will notify the Contractor well in advance of the dates for the wind-on final acceptance tests. The Contractor shall advise the Owner or the Engineer when the equipment is completed and ready for tests.<br>Upon satisfactory completion of the acceptance tests for the steel shell and components, and completion of all outstanding deficiencies, the equipment, in part or in full, will be accepted by the owner. The Owner will issue an Equipment Acceptance Certificate (EAC).</p>','Verbatim','2023-12-30 16:01:16','2023-12-30 16:07:11'),(11,8,8,2,4,3,1090,'Flexible Nozzle Plate Material Inspection Test',1,1,'QUAL','<p>This test is for material inspection of Flexible Nozzle plates (3).</p>','Verbatim','2024-01-01 11:45:45','2024-01-01 11:56:10');
